<subSubSection id="C33CA9C7FFA7FFD0A55EF43DB607CE2F" pageId="3" pageNumber="368" type="distribution">
<caption id="DF59AAC4FFA7FFD0A55EF43DB607CE2F" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6584712" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6584712" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6584712/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="368" targetBox="[1462,2053,2931,3344]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8B99FA4CFFA7FFD0A55EF43DB607CE2F" blockId="3.[2076,2668,2927,3350]" pageId="3" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis id="B952265EFFA7FFD0A55EF43DB7C4CE54" bold="true" box="[2076,2252,3041,3074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="368">Distribution.</emphasis>
Central African Republic, N DR Congo, South Sudan, and NW Uganda; presence in E Cameroon and NW Kenya is possible.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33CA9C7FFA7FFD0A55FF3A3B51BCF33" pageId="3" pageNumber="368" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B99FA4CFFA7FFD0A55FF3A3B51BCF33" blockId="3.[2076,2668,2927,3350]" lastBlockId="3.[1464,2666,3357,3468]" pageId="3" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis id="B952265EFFA7FFD0A55FF3A3B63DCEF6" bold="true" box="[2077,2357,3199,3232]" pageId="3" pageNumber="368">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 157-200 mm, tail 14-27 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. The Ochre Mole-rat is medium-sized. Its dorsal and ventral pelage is brown; head has white patch, with lightly colored areas around eyes. Vibrissae occur on feet and tail. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 44, FN = 76.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
